Solar Senior Capital Ltd. (SUNS) Ex-Dividend Date Scheduled for July 18, 2017


July 17, 2017, 09:00:05 AM EDT
By NASDAQ.com News









































Shutterstock photo


Solar Senior Capital Ltd. ( SUNS  ) will begin trading ex-dividend on July 18, 2017. A cash dividend payment of $0.117 per share is scheduled to be paid on August 01, 2017. Shareholders who purchased SUNS prior to the ex-dividend date are eligible for the cash dividend payment. This marks the 59th quarter that SUNS has paid the same dividend. At the current stock price of $17.34, the dividend yield is 8.13%. The previous trading day's last sale of SUNS was $17.34, representing a -6.07% decrease from the 52 week high of $18.46 and a 15.14% increase over the 52 week low of $15.06. SUNS's current earnings per share, an indicator of a company's profitability, is $1.57. Zacks Investment Research reports SUNS's forecasted earnings growth in 2017 as -1.17%, compared to an industry average of -6%. For more information on the declaration, record and payment dates, visit the SUNS Dividend History  page. Our  Dividend Calendar  has the full list of stocks that have an ex-dividend today.



The views and opinions expressed herein are the views and opinions of the author and do not necessarily reflect those of Nasdaq, Inc.











